hudson.tasks.Shell.command:
#!/bin/bash
aws s3 cp s3://avillach-biodatacatalyst-deployments-3drb48r/genomic-etl/ingestion-indexes/phs001607.c6_vcfIndex.tsv .
aws sts assume-role --duration-seconds 900 --role-arn arn:aws:iam::736265540791:role/dbgap-etl --role-session-name "jenkins" > assume-role-output.txt export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=`grep AccessKeyId assume-role-output.txt | cut -d ':' -f 2 | sed "s/[ ,\"]//g"` export AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=`grep SecretAccessKey assume-role-output.txt | cut -d ':' -f 2 | sed "s/[ ,\"]//g"` export AWS_SESSION_TOKEN=`grep SessionToken assume-role-output.txt | cut -d ':' -f 2 | sed "s/[ ,\"]//g"`
echo "$stdy_id ready to process, fetching subject and sample multi files and patient mapping" aws s3 cp s3://avillach-73-bdcatalyst-etl/ipf/decoded/ data/ --recursive --exclude "*" --include "*Sample.MULTI*" aws s3 cp s3://avillach-73-bdcatalyst-etl/ipf/decoded/ data/ --recursive --exclude "*" --include "*Subject.MULTI*"
aws s3 cp s3://avillach-73-bdcatalyst-etl/ipf/data/IPF_PatientMapping.v2.csv data/ --quiet
